Either you can install/downlaod all the packages individually
or
You can copy the above text and convert them into a text document, saving them as "env.yml".
and create a virtual environment using the command - 
(I am using conda environment so the code will run in conda prompt if you use any other software, you
can google how to make an environment from a 'yml' file)

Command - conda env create -f env.yml 





EERORS -
If you face any error while running the main python files related to keras,
try uninstalling and installing keras library again.